        "name": "The Chuhn (2025)",
        "seasonalEventType": "Chuhn",
        "img": "logos/chuhn-banner-2025.png",
        "lore": "A group of intergalactic merchants called the Chuhn have entered the galaxy to explore and trade. Their visit is temporary, and ships are encouraged to take advantage of new trading opportunities while they are passing through. The Chuhn visited once, long ago, and seem to know a few details about the galaxy's ancient history.<br><br>During The Chuhn visit, the following effects apply to the entire Galaxy:<br>Scrapping artifacts for Complex Tech Parts will yield additional parts.<br>All tariffs and auction charges have doubled.<br>Merchants that complete Daily Missions will earn bonus 'Star Chart Purger' artifacts.<br>When scanning for planets, you have a chance of receiving Complex Tech Parts based on your rank, or discovering a 'Market Interchange Beacon'.<br>Colonizing 'Average' or smaller planets will sometimes attract a 'Chuhn Orbital Freeport'.The 'Chuhn Ingress' Zone is available to influence.",
